First of all install ZeroMQ (http://www.zeromq.org/).


For building and running the API the following related projects are required:
1. mosaic-java-interoperability: http://mosaic.ieat.ro/hg/users/ciprian/mosaic-java-interoperability/
2. mosaic-java-tools: http://mosaic.ieat.ro/hg/users/ciprian/mosaic-java-tools/
3. jzmq: http://mosaic.ieat.ro/hg/users/ciprian/jzmq/
Download and build them. First, build jzmq. After that, copy the ZeroMQ libraries (libjzmq.so and libzmq.so.1.0.0) in the lib directory
under the zeromq module of the mosaic-java-interoperability project. Build the mosaic-java-tools and the mosaic-java-interoperability projects.

Finally, build the mOSAIC API.

